arubaWiredLldpMIB.name: arubaWiredLldpMIB
arubaWiredLldpMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
arubaWiredLldpMIB.description: This MIB module describes management objects that manage LLDP information related to Power Source Equipment (PSE). This is the MIB module related to HPE Aruba LLDP

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerTable.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerTable
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerTable.description: This table contains one row per port of power ethernet information (as a part of the LLDP 802.3bt organizational extension) on the local system known to this agent.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerEntry.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerEntry
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerEntry.description: Information about a particular port component.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPortClass.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPortClass
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPortClass.description: The value that identifies the port Class of the given port associated with the local system.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerMDISupported.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerMDISupported
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerMDISupported.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the MDI power is supported on the given port associated with the local system.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerMDIEnabled.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerMDIEnabled
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerMDIEnabled.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the MDI power is enabled on given port associated with the local system.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairControlab.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairControlable
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairControlab.description: The truth value used to indicate the ability to control which PSE Pinout Alternative is used for PD detection and power.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairs.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairs
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairs.description: The truth value that identifies the PSE Pinout Alternative in use for detecting and supplying power to the PD.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClass.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClass
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClass.description: The truth value that indicates the requested Class of the PD.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerType.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerType
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerType.description: This field reflects the actual local power type.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerSource.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerSource
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerSource.description: This field reflects the requested local device power source. When the power type is PSE, this field shall be set to primary(2) when the PSE is sourcing its power through the PI from its primary supply; to backup(3) when the PSE is sourcing its power through the PI from a backup source; and to unknown(1) when this information is not available.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPriority.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPriority
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPriority.description: This field reflects the requested local device power priority. When the power type is PD, this field shall be set to the power priority configured for the device. If a PD is unable to determine its power priority or it has not been configured, then this field shall be set to unknown(1). When the power type is PSE, this field shall be set to unknown(1).

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerVa.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerValue
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerVa.description: It indicates the maximum input average power the PD is requesting in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerVa.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerValueA
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerVa.description: It indicates the PD requested power value for the Mode A pairset in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerVa.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerValueB
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDRequestedPowerVa.description: It indicates the PD requested power value for the Mode B pairset in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerV.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerValue
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerV.description: It indicates the maximum input average power the PSE expects the PD to draw in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerV.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerValueA
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerV.description: It indicates the maximum input average power levels the PSE expects the dual-signature PD to draw, in units of 0.1 W, on Alternative A, when the PSE provides power over 4-pair.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerV.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerValueB
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAllocatedPowerV.description: It indicates the maximum input average power levels the PSE expects the dual-signature PD to draw, in units of 0.1 W, on Alternative B, when the PSE provides power over 4-pair.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEPoweringStatus.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEPoweringStatus
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEPoweringStatus.description: This field reflects the existing powering configuration of the PSE and thus indicates that the PSE is using the 'PSE allocated power value' field or is using the 'PSE allocated power value Alternative A' field and 'PSE allocated power value Alternative B' field. For a PD the contents of this attribute are undefined.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairsExt.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairsExt
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerPairsExt.description: This field indicates the supported PSE Pinout Alternative. For a PD the contents of this attribute are undefined

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExtA.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExtA
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExtA.description: For a dual-signature PD, it indicates the requested Class for Mode A during Physical Layer Classification. For a single-signature PD, a read-only value set to 'singlesig'. For a PSE connected to a dual-signature PD, a read-only value that indicates the currently assigned Class for Mode A. For a PSE connected to a single-signature PD, or a PSE that operates only in 2-pair mode, the value is set to 'singlesig'

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExtB.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExtB
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExtB.description: For a dual-signature PD, it indicates the requested Class for Mode B during Physical Layer Classification. For a single-signature PD, a read-only value set to 'singlesig'. For a PSE connected to a dual-signature PD, a read-only value that indicates the currently assigned Class for Mode B. For a PSE connected to a single-signature PD, or a PSE that operates only in 2-pair mode, the value is set to 'singlesig'

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExt.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExt
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerClassExt.description: For a single-signature PD, it indicates the requested Class during Physical Layer Classification. For a dual-signature PD, the value is set to 'dualsig'. For a PSE connected to a single-signature PD or a PSE that operates only in 2-pair mode, a readonly value that indicates the currently assigned Class. For a PSE connected to a dualsignature PD, a read-only value set to 'dualsig'.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerTypeExt.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerTypeExt
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPowerTypeExt.description: This field indicates if the local system is a Type 3 or Type 4 PSE or PD, and in the case of a Type 3 or Type 4 PD, if it is a single-signature PD or a dual-signature PD

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDLoad.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDLoad
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPDLoad.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the load of a dual- signature PD is electrically isolated. For a single-signature PD, or a PSE, the value of this attribute is FALSE.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEMaxAvailPower.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEMaxAvailPower
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEMaxAvailPower.description: It indicates the local PSE maximum available power value in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAutoclassSuppor.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAutoclassSupport
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocPSEAutoclassSuppor.description: It indicates whether the local PSE system supports Autoclass

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocAutoclassCompleted.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocAutoclassCompleted
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocAutoclassCompleted.description: It indicates whether the local PSE system has completed the Autoclass measurement

arubaWiredLldpLocPseTlvSentType.name: arubaWiredLldpLocPseTlvSentType
arubaWiredLldpLocPseTlvSentType.description: This field specifies the set of TLVs that are actually sent by the PSE

arubaWiredLldpLocPdTlvSentType.name: arubaWiredLldpLocPdTlvSentType
arubaWiredLldpLocPdTlvSentType.description: This field specifies the set of TLVs that are actually sent by the PD

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerTable.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerTable
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerTable.description: This table contains one row per port of power ethernet information (as a part of the LLDP 802.3bt organizational extension) on the remote system known to this agent.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerEntry.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerEntry
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerEntry.description: Information about a particular port component.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPortClass.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPortClass
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPortClass.description: The value that identifies the port Class of the given port associated with the remote system.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerMDISupported.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerMDISupported
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerMDISupported.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the MDI power is supported on the given port associated with the remote system.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerMDIEnabled.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerMDIEnabled
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerMDIEnabled.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the MDI power is enabled on given port associated with the remote system.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPairControlab.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPairControlable
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPairControlab.description: The truth value used to indicate the ability to control which PSE Pinout Alternative is used for PD detection and power.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPairs.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPairs
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPairs.description: The truth value that identifies the PSE Pinout Alternative in use for detecting and supplying power to the PD.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClass.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClass
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClass.description: The truth value that indicates the requested Class of the PD.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerType.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerType
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerType.description: This field reflects the actual remote power type.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerSource.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerSource
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerSource.description: This field reflects the remote device (PD) requested power source. This field is encoded as pseAndLocal(4) when a PD being powered both locally and by a PSE, to local(3) when the PD being powered locally only, and to pse(2) when the PD is being powered by a PSE

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPriority.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPriority
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerPriority.description: This field reflects the requested remote device power priority. When the power type is PD, this field shall be set to the power priority configured for the device. If a PD is unable to determine its power priority or it has not been configured, then this field shall be set to unknown(1). When the power type is PSE, this field shall be set to unknown(1).

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerVa.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerValue
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerVa.description: It indicates the maximum input average power the PD is requesting in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerVa.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerValueA
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerVa.description: It indicates the PD requested power value for the Mode A pairset in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerVa.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerValueB
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDRequestedPowerVa.description: It indicates the PD requested power value for the Mode B pairset in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerV.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerValue
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerV.description: It indicates the PSE allocated power value received from the remote system. For a PSE, it is the PSE allocated power value that was echoed back by the remote PD, in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerV.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerValueA
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerV.description: It indicates the PSE allocated power value for the Alternative A pairset received from the remote system. For a PSE, it is the PSE allocated power value for the Alternative A pairset that was echoed back by the remote PD, in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerV.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerValueB
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEAllocatedPowerV.description: It indicates the PSE allocated power value for the Alternative B pairset received from the remote system. For a PSE, it is the PSE allocated power value for the Alternative A pairset that was echoed back by the remote PD, in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDPoweredStatus.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDPoweredStatus
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDPoweredStatus.description: This field indicates the existing powered configuration of the PD and thus indicate that the PD is using the 'PD requested power value' field or is using the 'PD requested power value Mode A' field and the 'PD requested power value Mode B' field. For a PSE the contents of this attribute are undefined.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExtA.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExtA
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExtA.description: For a dual-signature PD, a read-only value that indicates the currently assigned Class for Mode A by the remote 4-pair PSE. For a single-signature PD, or a dual-signature PD connected to a 2-pair only PSE, a read-only value set to 'singlesig' by the remote PSE. For a PSE connected to a dualsignature PD, a read-only value that indicates the requested Class for Mode A during Physical Layer classification by the remote PD. For a PSE connected to a single-signature PD, a read-only value set to 'singlesig' by the remote PD

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExtB.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExtB
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExtB.description: For a dual-signature PD, a read-only value that indicates the currently assigned Class for Mode A by the remote 4-pair PSE. For a single-signature PD, or a dual-signature PD connected to a 2-pair only PSE, a read-only value set to 'singlesig' by the remote PSE. For a PSE connected to a dualsignature PD, a read-only value that indicates the requested Class for Mode B during Physical Layer classification by the remote PD. For a PSE connected to a single-signature PD, a read-only value set to 'singlesig' by the remote PD.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExt.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExt
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerClassExt.description: For a single-signature PD or a dual-signature PD connected to a 2-pair only PSE, a read-only value that indicates the currently assigned Class by the remote PSE. For a dual- signature PD connected to a 4-pair capable PSE, a read-only value set to 'dualsig' by the remote PSE. For a PSE connected to a single-signature PD, a read-only value that indicates the requested Class during Physical Layer classification by the remote PD. For a PSE connected to a dual-signature PD, a readonly value set to 'dualsig' by the remote PD.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerTypeExt.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerTypeExt
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerTypeExt.description: This field indicates if the remote system is a Type 3 or Type 4 PSE or PD, and in the case of a Type 3 or Type 4 PD, if it is a single-signature PD or dual-signature PD

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDLoad.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDLoad
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPDLoad.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the load of the remote dual-signature PD is electrically isolated. For a PD this attribute is set to FALSE

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPD4PID.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPD4PID
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPD4PID.description: The truth value used to indicate whether the remote PD system supports powering of both PD Modes

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEMaxAvailPower.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEMaxAvailPower
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPSEMaxAvailPower.description: It indicates the remote PSE maximum available power value in units of 0.1 W.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemAutoclassRequest.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemAutoclassRequest
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemAutoclassRequest.description: It indicates whether the remote PD system is requesting an Autoclass measurement

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerDownRequest.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerDownRequest
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerDownRequest.description: It indicates that the remote PD system is requesting a power down when the value is 0x1D

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerDownTime.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerDownTime
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemPowerDownTime.description: It indicates the number of seconds the remote PD requests to stay powered off. A value of zero indicates an indefinite amount of time.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3Compliance.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3Compliance
arubaWiredLldpXdot3Compliance.description: The compliance statement for LLDP implementation.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocSysGroup.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocSysGroup
arubaWiredLldpXdot3LocSysGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent LLDP 802.3 organizational extension for POEP Local Device Information. This group is mandatory for agents which implement the LLDP 802.3 organizational extension for POEP.

arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemSysGroup.name: arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemSysGroup
arubaWiredLldpXdot3RemSysGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent LLDP 802.3 organizational extension for POEP Remote Device Information. This group is mandatory for agents which implement the LLDP 802.3 organizational extension for POEP.
